Casper H.S. Dik (casper@fwi.uva.nl) writes:

> There was another such ``card'' touted as the ``final solution'' to
> virus (to use the correct latin plural, the u is long) by a Dutch
> company.  If you can copy applications, you ca infect them.

There is no correct Latin plural of the word 'virus'. It is a word
(meaning 'poison', BTW) which does not have a plural - like 'air' in
English. See the FAQ for Virus-L/comp.virus.

Are you talking about Thunderbyte? Yes, I agree with you; there are
several ways to infect a system protected by it.

